Of course. I've identified a critical security issue in the `AddMemberLeague` component. It's attempting to handle passwords manually, but the database has been correctly updated to use Supabase's secure authentication system. Storing passwords directly is unsafe and will cause the form to fail.

I'll refactor the component to use `supabase.auth.signUp`, which is the correct and secure way to create users. This involves adding an email field to the form and updating the submission logic.

Additionally, I'll create the necessary database migrations to link user profiles to their auth identity and update the storage security policies as you requested.

