  Fix: Create an insert policy for league_members

If you want to allow inserts for everyone (not recommended for production), run:

-- Enable RLS if not already enabled
ALTER TABLE league_members ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Allow inserts for all users
CREATE POLICY "Allow all inserts"
ON league_members
FOR INSERT
WITH CHECK (true);

 Example: Safer policy (only authenticated users can insert their own row)

If your league_members table has a column like owner_id (users auth.uid), then:

CREATE POLICY "Users can insert their own member profile"
ON league_members
FOR INSERT
WITH CHECK (auth.uid() = owner_id);


 This way, a logged-in user can only insert a row where owner_id matches their Supabase auth UID.
Since you removed email/auth, you may not want this  unless you reintroduce owner_id.

 Example: Validate fields at insert

If you want to enforce your business rules (like NID must be 18 digits):

CREATE POLICY "Insert valid NID"
ON league_members
FOR INSERT
WITH CHECK (char_length(national_id_number) = 18);

